about.description: pyvisfile lets you write new-style Vtk visualization files.

name: pyvisfile
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "pyvisfile" %}
{% set version = "2016.1" %}
{% set sha256 = "1b1f4eec567b2a16893e61c7b36f2ecf63823dad12a802ef5427a243e44795fb" %}

package:
    name: {{ name|lower }}
    version: {{ version }}

source:
    fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
    sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
    number: 0
    script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
    build:
        - python
        - setuptools
    run:
        - python
        - numpy
        - pytools
        - six

test:
    imports:
        - {{ name }}

about:
    home: http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pyvisfile
    dev_url: http://github.com/inducer/pyvisfile
    doc_url: https://documen.tician.de/pyvisfile
    license: MIT
    license_file: LICENSE
    summary: Large-scale Visualization Data Storage
    description: |
        pyvisfile lets you write new-style Vtk visualization files.

extra:
    recipe-maintainers:
        - inducer
